            <div class="about-details-container">
                <div class="text-container">
                    <p>
                        Before I ever worked in technology, I worked the line in professional kitchens—where pressure was constant, timing was critical, and mistakes were visible immediately. In that environment, you learn discipline. You learn communication. Most importantly, you learn how to remain steady when everything around you accelerates. Those lessons have defined my professional identity.
                        <br /><br />
                        Transitioning into technology as a Technical Support Analyst at Canon Information Technology Services felt natural. Enterprise systems, like kitchens, are ecosystems—each component dependent on another. When something breaks, the solution requires both technical understanding and operational awareness. I troubleshoot proprietary software, hardware environments, and enterprise applications by systematically isolating variables, reviewing system behaviors, and guiding issues through structured resolution.
                        <br /><br />
                        My approach to troubleshooting is intentional. I do not react—I analyze. I assess severity, understand user impact, gather relevant evidence, and determine whether the issue is environmental, configuration-based, user-driven, or systemic. I maintain meticulous documentation and communicate clearly at every stage because transparency builds trust, especially during escalations.
                        <br /><br />
                        What differentiates me is the intersection of soft skills and technical execution. I understand urgency without panic. I value collaboration over isolation. I see technical problems not as disruptions, but as systems revealing weaknesses that can be improved.
                        <br /><br />
                        My journey from the intensity of professional kitchens to enterprise technical environments reflects adaptability, resilience, and growth. I bring composure under pressure, disciplined troubleshooting, and a strong service mindset to every challenge.
                    </p>
                </div>
